rder for it to escape from local minima"],"metadata":{"id":"HFG9pKdOmWBz"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## 3 Polinomial Regression\n"],"metadata":{"id":"LYrtl3QVgk34"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["What if your data is actually more complex than a simple straight line? A simple way to do this is to add powers of each feature as new features, then train a linear model on this extended set of features. This technique is called **Polynomial Regression**."],"metadata":{"id":"Yvzx-VdUgqTJ"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from sklearn.preprocessing import PolynomialFeatures\n","from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n","import pandas as pd\n","\n","poly_features = PolynomialFeatures(degree=2, include_bias=False)\n","X_poly = poly_features.fit_transform(X)\n","\n","poly_reg = LinearRegression()\n","poly_reg.fit(X_poly,y)\n","\n","pd.Series(poly_reg.coef_.ravel(), index = poly_features.get_feature_names_out(X.design_info.column_names))"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":523},"id":"eYJwYGgli91S","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1771451798974,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":50,"user":{"displayName":"Ben Xue","userId":"08600776733826581408"}},"outputId":"89fb6e92-8231-45f5-e0e7-2f969322302b"},"execution_count":61,"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["Intercept           0.000000e+00\n","educ               -3.760924e-01\n","exper               8.786756e-02\n","tenure             -1.247648e-02\n","Intercept^2        -3.986395e-15\n","Intercept educ     -3.760924e-01\n","Intercept exper     8.786756e-02\n","Intercept tenure   -1.247648e-02\n","educ^2              4.938336e-02\n","educ exper          1.025214e-04\n","educ tenure         2.196122e-02\n","exper^2            -3.702404e-03\n","exper tenure       -3.779960e-04\n","tenure^2           -2.631162e-03\n","dtype: float64"],"text/html":["<div>\n","<style scoped>\n","    .dataframe tbody tr th:only-of-type {\n","        vertical-align: mid